(3) Civil citation means
a noncriminal notice which cannot result in a criminal record and is described
in section 43-248.02;

(4) Cost
or costs means (a) the sum or equivalent expended, paid, or charged for goods
or services, or expenses incurred, or (b) the contracted or negotiated price;

(5) Criminal street gang means
a group of three or more people with a common identifying name, sign, or symbol
whose group identity or purposes include engaging in illegal activities;

(6) Criminal street gang member
means a person who willingly or voluntarily becomes and remains a member of
a criminal street gang;

(11) Mental health facility
means a treatment facility as defined in section 71-914 or a government, private,
